## System Role

`agent-config` is the global configuration repository for Claude Code. It defines:
1. How the AI orchestrates SDD workflows and delegates to sub-agents
2. The skill catalog covering SDD phases, meta-tools, and tech stacks
3. The project management lifecycle — setup, audit, fix, update

## Two-Layer Deployment

```
agent-config (repo)          ~/.claude/ (runtime)
      │                              │
      ├── CLAUDE.md    ──install──►  ├── CLAUDE.md
      ├── skills/      ──install──►  ├── skills/
      ├── settings.json ─install──►  ├── settings.json
      ├── hooks/       ──install──►  ├── hooks/
      ├── openspec/    ──install──►  ├── openspec/
      └── ai-context/  ──install──►  └── ai-context/
                            ◄──sync────  (memory/ only)
```

- `install.sh`: repo → `~/.claude/` (all directories, one-directional)
- `sync.sh`: `~/.claude/memory/` → `repo/memory/` (memory capture only, reverse direction)

## Skill Architecture

Every skill is a directory with a single `SKILL.md` entry point. Skills declare their structural format via frontmatter:

| `format:` value | Required main section | Used for |
|-----------------|----------------------|---------|
| `procedural` (default) | `## Process` | SDD phases, meta-tools, orchestrators |
| `reference` | `## Patterns` or `## Examples` | Technology and library skills |
| `anti-pattern` | `## Anti-patterns` | Anti-pattern catalog skills |

### Skill placement tiers

- **Global** (`~/.claude/skills/`) — available across all projects on the machine
- **Project-local** (`.claude/skills/`) — versioned alongside project source code; must be committed to repo

Resolution order: project-local → config override (`openspec/config.yaml skill_overrides`) → global catalog.

## Inter-Skill Communication

Skills communicate exclusively via file artifacts. No in-memory state passing between skills.

| Artifact | Producer | Consumer | Location |
|----------|---------|---------|----------|
| `audit-report.md` | project-audit | project-fix | `.claude/audit-report.md` in project |
| `analysis-report.md` | project-analyze | project-audit, user | project root |
| `openspec/changes/*/proposal.md` | sdd-propose | sdd-spec, sdd-design | `openspec/changes/<name>/` |
| `openspec/changes/*/design.md` | sdd-design | sdd-tasks | `openspec/changes/<name>/` |
| `openspec/changes/*/tasks.md` | sdd-tasks | sdd-apply | `openspec/changes/<name>/` |
| `openspec/changes/*/verify-report.md` | sdd-verify | user, sdd-archive | `openspec/changes/<name>/` |
| `ai-context/*.md` | memory-init / memory-update | all skills | `ai-context/` in project |

## Key Architectural Decisions

1. **Skills are directories, not files** — allows co-locating templates, examples, or sub-skills
2. **SKILL.md is the convention** — every skill directory has exactly one entry point
3. **Artifacts over in-memory state** — skills communicate via files, never via conversation context alone
4. **install.sh is repo-authoritative** — all directories flow repo → `~/.claude/`; the only reverse direction is `sync.sh` for memory only; never edit `~/.claude/` directly
5. **Two-tier skill placement model** — global for machine-wide skills, project-local for project-specific skills; project-local takes precedence
6. **solid-ddd is a universal design principles skill** — loaded unconditionally for all non-documentation code changes; not keyword-triggered like tech skills
7. **sdd-apply enforces a structured Quality Gate** — 7-item gate (SRP, abstraction, DIP, domain model integrity, ISP, no scope creep, no over-engineering) evaluated before marking each task complete; QUALITY_VIOLATION is non-blocking by default
8. **sdd-apply mandates a Diagnosis Step before every task** — read files, run read-only diagnostics, write a structured DIAGNOSIS block before any file write
9. **sdd-apply enforces a per-task retry circuit breaker** — max 3 attempts (configurable); task marked `[BLOCKED]` on failure; same-strategy detection prevents infinite identical retries
10. **sdd-tasks classifies warnings as MUST_RESOLVE or ADVISORY** — MUST_RESOLVE blocks apply execution; ADVISORY is logged only
11. **sdd-verify enforces an evidence gate** — `verify-report.md` must include a `## Tool Execution` section; `[x]` criteria require verifiable evidence, not abstract reasoning
12. **Feedback sessions produce only proposals** — never SDD implementation; two-session model enforced in CLAUDE.md Unbreakable Rules
13. **Always-on intent classification** — every user message classified into Meta-Command, Change Request, Exploration, or Question (ADR-029); classification gate runs before any response
14. **SDD parallelism bounded at 2 concurrent tasks** — only safe parallel pair is sdd-spec + sdd-design (non-overlapping file sets); documented in ADR-028
15. **sdd-new and sdd-ff auto-infer change slug** — stop-word-filtered algorithm, max 5 words, lowercase hyphenated, date-prefixed; no manual name input gate
16. **Runtime-auditing skill is standalone** — claude-folder-audit audits `~/.claude/` as a standalone skill, not as a project-audit dimension; report written to `~/.claude/claude-folder-audit-report.md`
17. **SDD phase skills load project context as Step 0** — all 6 SDD phase skills read ai-context/ files before producing output; missing files are non-blocking INFO notes

